{
  "texts": [
    "It serves as an unbiased assessment of how well the trained model generalizes to unseen data.",
    "For this case, a similar logic can be applied.",
    "Setting aside a portion of the available dataset as holdout data, we can evaluate the model's classification capabilities.",
    "First taking a sample of the data and hand-coding it independently of the results from the LLM, we then compare our results to the LLM's results and qualitatively assess the discrepancy to determine if it is significant.",
    "Ultimately, holdout data acts as a vital benchmark for selecting the bestperforming model and ensures the reliability and effectiveness of machine learning solutions in practical applications (Dwork et al., 2015)."
  ]
}